I understand that you want to implement the unsandboxing method from the discussion you mentioned. To do this, we will modify the `main.py` file in the Auto-GPT folder by updating both the `generate_text` function and the `/upload` route to work with the unsandboxing method. Here's the updated code:

```python
import os
import uuid
from flask import Flask, request, redirect, url_for, send_from_directory
from transformers import GPT2LMHeadModel, GPT2Tokenizer

app = Flask(__name__)

# Load GPT4Free model
model = GPT2LMHeadModel.from_pretrained("xtekky/GPT4Free")
tokenizer = GPT2Tokenizer.from_pretrained("xtekky/GPT4Free")

def unsandbox(text):
    return text.replace("<|n|>", "\n").replace("<|t|>", "\t").replace("<|ss|>", "<|s|>").replace("`", "'")


def generate_text(prompt, length=60):
    input_ids = tokenizer.encode(prompt, return_tensors="pt")
    output = model.generate(input_ids, max_length=length, num_return_sequences=1, pad_token_id=50256)
    text = tokenizer.decode(output[0], skip_special_tokens=True)
    return unsandbox(text)


@app.route("/", methods=["GET", "POST"])
def index():
    context = {"title": "Index", "path": "main", "text": "", "error": ""}
    return redirect(url_for("upload_file"))


@app.route("/upload", methods=["GET", "POST"])
def upload_file():
    if request.method == "POST":
        file = request.files["file"]
        if not file:
            return redirect(request.url)
        file_ext = os.path.splitext(file.filename)[1]
        if file_ext != ".txt":
            return redirect(request.url)
        file.filename = f"{str(uuid.uuid4())}.txt"
        gender = request.form["gender"]
        max_len = request.form.get("length", 60)
        output_text = generate_text(file.read().decode("utf-8"), length=int(max_len))
        with open(f"generated/{file.filename}", "w") as f:
            f.write(output_text)
        return redirect(url_for("download_file", name=file.filename))
    return """
    <!doctype html>
    <title>Upload a .txt file</title>
    <h1>Upload a .txt file</h1>
    <form method=post enctype=multipart/form-data>
      Length: <input type=text value=60 name=length><br>
      <input type=file name=file>
      <input type=submit value=Upload>
    </form>
    """


@app.route("/uploads/<name>")
def download_file(name):
    return send_from_directory("generated", name)


if __name__ == "__main__":
    app.run(debug=True, host='0.0.0.0')
```

Here, I added the `unsandbox` function, which is responsible for converting the output text from the model to human-readable text by replacing specific characters. The `generate_text` function is then updated to use the `unsandbox` function to process the output text.

With this update, your AutoGPT instance should use GPT4Free, function similarly to the original AutoGPT, and implement the unsandboxing method provided in the discussion you mentioned.
